casebody.data:
ROBERTOY v. MICHIGAN. No. 308,

Misc.

Decided December 19, 1960. Petitioner pro se. Paul L. Adams, Attorney General of Michigan, and Samuel J. Torina, Solicitor General, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The appeal is dismissed for the reason that the judgment of the Supreme Court of Michigan, sought here to be reviewed, is based upon a nonfederal ground adequate to support it.
